    public interface TypeSafeKey<T>
    An interface representing a parametrized key for use in HMaps. The parameter specifies the type of the value stored at this binding inside the HMap.

    This is intentionally an interface so user-defined implementations are possible; however, it's important to note that all hopes of type-safety hinge on equality being implemented such that no two TypeSafeKeys with differing parameters may be considered equal. Reference equality is used here as the default, as that is sufficient.
